{"type":"message","id":"5a7cdfad","parentId":"74860705","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:45:46.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still the same license issue. Both the original and backup license files have corrupted/invalid digital signature. This is a license activation issue that can't be fixed just by restoring the backup. \n\nThe user's TOOLS.md mentions \"运行需要管理员权限（Unity 许可证校验）\", suggesting running as admin should fix it. But the issue seems deeper - the actual ULF license file has an invalid digital signature.\n\nLet me try running a scheduled task with highest privileges to see if that helps.\n\nActually, maybe I should try to re-activate the license. Let me check if Unity Hub can help activate it. Or maybe run a license activation command.\n\nLet me try another approach: create a scheduled task to run the bat with highest privileges (SYSTEM level).","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_vQvkewj2Dx58s2uFwsfc8249","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if we can delete the licensing client and let it be recreated\n# First, check the actual license file content\nGet-Content \"C:\\ProgramData\\Unity\\Unity_lic.ulf\" -TotalCount 5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":801,"output":243,"cacheRead":16896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17940,"cost":{"input":0.00011214000000000001,"output":0.00006804,"cacheRead":0.000473088,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000653268}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778755543221,"responseId":"3bc7f58a-2acf-41e9-9b76-4a63f4c610bf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"90648edc","parentId":"5a7cdfad","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:45:46.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_vQvkewj2Dx58s2uFwsfc8249","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<root>\r\n  <License id=\"Terms\">\r\n    <MachineBindings>\r\n      <Binding Key=\"1\" Value=\"00329-00000-00003-AA082\"/>\r\n      <Binding Key=\"2\" Value=\"00523_B8_5133B6_ED.1\"/>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":246,"aggregated":"<root>\r\n  <License id=\"Terms\">\r\n    <MachineBindings>\r\n      <Binding Key=\"1\" Value=\"00329-00000-00003-AA082\"/>\r\n      <Binding Key=\"2\" Value=\"00523_B8_5133B6_ED.1\"/>","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778755546642}}
{"type":"message","id":"b614afe2","parentId":"90648edc","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:45:49.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The license file exists and has content. The digital signature is invalid, meaning the file might be corrupted or from an older Unity version. Let me start Unity Hub to see if it can re-activate the license. Or try to manually clear the license and have Unity re-activate.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach: run the Unity license activation through the command line.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Rfop8Haa4kCb1axqTtEA8220","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try manually activating via Unity's built-in license activation\n# First, kill any remaining licensing client processes\nGet-Process Unity* -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\n# Get the license file content for the activation code\nWrite-Host \"License file exists, checking corruption...\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\n$lic = Get-Content \"C:\\ProgramData\\Unity\\Unity_lic.ulf\" -Raw\nWrite-Host \"License file size: $($lic.Length) bytes\"\nWrite-Host \"Last line of file: $($lic.Trim().Substring([Math]::Max(0, $lic.Trim().Length - 100)))\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":99,"output":260,"cacheRead":17920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18279,"cost":{"input":0.000013860000000000001,"output":0.00007280000000000001,"cacheRead":0.00050176,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00058842}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778755546643,"responseId":"9bfd0d2c-4de1-4c86-96c1-14c89ed18a49"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a780d51a","parentId":"b614afe2","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:45:49.704Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Rfop8Haa4kCb1axqTtEA8220","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"License file exists, checking corruption...\nLicense file size: 2617 bytes\nLast line of file: NsAsRxRX83rl0+wt3KXxtTFD74M6Sd/XNAyMkmCTo0ixPAKNXqh1HRg96CA=</SignatureValue>\n  </Signature>\n</root>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":287,"aggregated":"License file exists, checking corruption...\nLicense file size: 2617 bytes\nLast line of file: NsAsRxRX83rl0+wt3KXxtTFD74M6Sd/XNAyMkmCTo0ixPAKNXqh1HRg96CA=</SignatureValue>\n  </Signature>\n</root>","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778755549704}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca132cb8","parentId":"a780d51a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:45:54.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The license file seems to have a Signature block. The issue is that Unity 2020.3.49f1 on this machine can't validate the license file correctly. This is a known issue with Unity Hub's licensing system.\n\nLet me try using the Unity Hub to activate the license. Or better, try running the Unity via the Hub rather than directly.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach: use `schtasks` to create a scheduled task that runs with highest privileges (SYSTEM) to start Unity. This might bypass the license check because the license might be stored per-user and SYSTEM can use any user's license.\n\nNo, that won't work either. The license issue is with the ULF file's digital signature being invalid.\n\nLet me check if there's a Unity Hub installation that might have the correct license cached.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QzaRnvWIo6xjYTaFzZUV9033","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check Unity Hub status\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\Unity\\config\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName, Length, LastWriteTime\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n# Check if Unity Hub is installed\nGet-ItemProperty \"HKLM:\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\*\" | Where-Object { $_.DisplayName -like \"*Unity*\" } | Select-Object DisplayName, InstallLocation\n# Check for Hub\nif (Test-Path \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\Unity\\hub\") { Write-Host \"Unity Hub user data found\" }\nif (Test-Path \"$env:PROGRAMDATA\\Unity Hub\") { Write-Host \"Unity Hub program data found\" }"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":186,"output":377,"cacheRead":18176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18739,"cost":{"input":0.00002604,"output":0.00010556000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000508928,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000640528}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778755549705,"responseId":"5e93b4fb-c225-41ea-98da-e941322ac927"}}
