{"type":"message","id":"38c680c6","parentId":"0f84db25","timestamp":"2026-05-14T10:47:37.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the license file was recreated but with the exact same size and timestamp as before. This means Unity Hub restored it from cache, not re-activated. The digital signature is still invalid.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Maybe the issue is specific to this Unity version. Let me try using the `-createManualActivationFile` flag to create a manual activation file, and then use the license file from a different method.\n\nActually, let me check if there's a way to use the Unity Hub to force re-activation. Or maybe I should try the licensing client directly.\n\nWait, I just had an idea. The TOOLS.md says `2020.3.49f1` but the actual folder on disk is `2020.3.49f1` (no `c1` suffix), yet the Unity binary reports it's built from `2020.3/china_unity/release` branch and version `2020.3.49f1c1`. This is the China version of Unity. The China version uses a different licensing mechanism than the regular one.\n\nLet me check if there's a specific license for the China version.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_mt5TItFGpVDiIcXdOH342070","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Kill all Unity processes first\nGet-Process \"Unity Hub\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\nGet-Process \"Unity\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\nGet-Process \"Unity.Licensing.Client\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 3\n\n# Try using manual activation approach for China Unity\n# Check if there's any license key stored\nWrite-Host \"=== Checking for serial/license keys ===\"\n$serialPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\*serial*\"\nGet-ChildItem $serialPath -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name\n# Check registry\nWrite-Host \"=== Registry keys ===\"\nGet-ItemProperty \"HKCU:\\Software\\Unity Technologies\\*\\*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue 2>&1 | Out-Null\nGet-Item \"HKCU:\\Software\\Unity\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Property -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":151,"output":531,"cacheRead":22656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23338,"cost":{"input":0.00002114,"output":0.00014868000000000002,"cacheRead":0.000634368,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000804188}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778755651888,"responseId":"b6562718-c0d3-4eb6-a372-f4b2f26101b5"}}
